txt.en: 'Here are your dwarves and the [placeholder] you seek.'
'Gúrbarash, I am honoured you have come to Sundergrót on behalf of Gundabad.'
'I let my Orcs camp at your halls, and now many are slain!'
'Lies! A pathetic attempt to explain your own failures.'
Instance: The Secrets of Sundergrót
'Stop talking so that we can hear them.'
'Gah!'
'I, I can explain!'
'Gundabad has nothing to gain from adding Sundergrót to its horde.'
'There are dwarves here! Great numbers in the hills, it must be!'
'I see with my own eyes what is here and my decision is final.'
'[placeholder], we found the meeting.'
'Now is our chance! Let us attack!'
'Gúrbarash, come back!'
'The offer of my Sundergrót forces swearing allegiance to Gundabad still stands.'
'Then Gundabad won't even accept my allegiance?!'
'Come my Orcs, we leave this pitiful place.'
'Look no further, vile goblin.'
'No need! I see these all empty, and the goblins I do see are injured!'
'I was told you had an army, a sizeable force, in your Sundergrót.'
'No! First I get kicked out of Goblin-town for siding with the Frost-horde!'
'There is nothing to explain, Rákhrum.'
'The wretch flees! Let him run.'
'You! I'll kill you all!'
'Keep quiet.'
'What I see in these halls is pitiful.'
'Gah! If only I found those dwarves and the [placeholder] mucking about in my halls.'
